race.comment: DON'TCALLMEKATHY (5) just missed here over this trip near the back of her initial campaign and resumed with a 2.5L defeat at Kembla Grange also at 1400m when she led. She will use the inside barrier and is thrown in with the 4kg claim. Has more up her sleeve and is sure to take catching. PAWA (8) went close at Mudgee first-up and then was sharply better when just missing a place at Hawkesbury. Fitter again and is well placed back to country level. SHERIFF'S STAR (4) is a Sydney-trained improver ready to show more like his best. Presents on an 8-day backup. SHARE THE JOY (6) has been disappointing since the Hawkesbury placing and may go better with the two gear tweaks.
